column5: Just got back today and the fishing started big yesterday, lot of big walleyes, 3 to 6 pounds, all the spawning is now over and the fishes are moving back to the lakes, looks like a very good beginning all over the reservoir, we saw lot of catches as well on the west and east side or the reservoir. Might be a good year to look forward to
Alces Dont let these guys catch all the nice walleyes now save us some for July. Atlanta Dave
